# Normalize all text files to LF on checkin, checkout as LF regardless of
# platform. Without this, files committed from a Windows checkout (no
# .gitattributes existed before this) end up with CRLF while files
# committed from Linux/macOS end up LF, purely by accident of which
# machine wrote them last -- this repo had exactly that split (Python,
# TOML, Markdown, and workflow YAML all mixed CRLF/LF) before this file
# was added. LF is the right default for a project whose CI, containers,
# and target audience are predominantly Unix.
* text=auto eol=lf
